I ordered from here via Uber eats, thinking I can indulge into a warm & toasty pizza to support local businesses during these times. However, when the pizza came in my hotel- it had a little label stating that it " needs to be heated in the oven". The pizza was obviously freshly made the morning off, which I don't have an issue with. The issue I have is that I am healthcare worker visiting NYC to help with the COVID-19 pandemic. Hotels don't even have microwaves or refrigerators; yet alone ovens to heat a pizza.  I am super disappointed- word of advise if your shipping the pizza to a hotel during these times, please have it ready to go for customers to eat. Maybe on your website, social media platforms please let customers know the pizza is cold and must need oven heated.

It is all done with a passion. Our servant was not only a good waitress, but a funny one as well. I can tell he likes his job and rightfully so. The seats we picked were in the back of the restaurant, which has an outdoor theme minus the view. Now the pizza was phenomenal. I am extremely critical with pizzas as they are at the top of my food chain and boy did they delivered. Every bite was filled evenly to the core. I understand why the chef takes his time making it. He treats his pizzas with care and it shows. I had a custom white pizza with spinach and my wife had a pie with pepperoni. Excellent service and excellent food. I said we could become a regular but will not be interested. I will not be returning to that pizzeria again. The pizza was good though.
